ctured way.\n2. **Manage** the conversations and information exchanged with the notebook.\n3. **Use** the responses from the notebook to perform tasks, answer questions, or generate content.\n4. **Improve** the overall performance and accuracy of the application.\n\nIn simple terms, LangChain is like a blueprint or a set of instructions that helps developers build applications that can effectively communicate with large language models, making it easier to create powerful and useful AI-powered tools.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":34},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"5. Simple Chain","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.003039,"end_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:30.134775+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:30.131736+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"from langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser\n\nchain = prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()\n\nresult = chain.invoke({\"topic\": \"AI Agents\"})\nprint(result)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-13T07:34:55.125735Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-13T07:34:55.126099Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-13T07:34:56.395475Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-13T07:34:55.126056Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-13T07:34:56.394599Z"},"papermill":{"duration":1.375507,"end_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:31.513578+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:30.138071+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[],"trusted":true},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"**What is an AI Agent.**\nAn AI agent is a computer program that can perform tasks on its own, using artificial intelligence (AI) to make decisions and take actions. Think of it like a robot that can think and act for itself.\n\n**Key Characteristics:**\n\n1. **Autonomy**: AI agents can work independently, without human intervention.\n2. **Decision-making**: They can make decisions based on the information they have and the goals they're trying to achieve.\n3. **Action**: They can take actions to achieve their goals, like moving, communicating, or solving problems.\n4. **Learning**: Many AI agents can learn from their experiences and improve over time.\n\n**Examples of AI Agents:**\n\n1. **Virtual Assistants**: Like Siri, Alexa, or Google Assistant, which can understand voice commands and perform tasks.\n2. **Self-Driving Cars**: Which use AI to navigate roads, avoid obstacles, and make decisions.\n3. **Chatbots**: That can have conversations with humans, answer questions, and provide customer support.\n4. **Game-playing Agents**: Like those that play chess, poker, or other games, using AI to make moves and win.\n\n**How AI Agents Work:**\n\n1. **Perception**: The agent receives information from its environment, like sensors or data.\n2. **Reasoning**: The agent uses this information to make decisions and choose actions.\n3. **Action**: The agent takes the chosen action, like moving or communicating.\n4. **Feedback**: The agent receives feedback on the outcome of its actions, which helps it learn and improve.\n\nIn simple terms, AI agents are like smart robots that can think, act, and learn on their own, using artificial intelligence to achieve their goals.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":35},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"6. Agent with tool","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.003011,"end_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:31.519843+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:31.516832+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"from langchain_core.tools import tool\nfrom langgraph.prebuilt import create_react_agent\n\n@tool\ndef convert_usd_to_inr(usd: float) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Convert USD to INR using a fixed exchange rate of 1 USD = 83 INR.\"\"\"\n    inr = usd * 83\n    return f\"${usd:.2f} is approximately ₹{inr:.2f}\"\n\n@tool\ndef calculate_emi(principal: float, annual_rate: float, months: int) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Calculate monthly EMI for a loan using principal, annual interest rate, and duration.\"\"\"\n    monthly_rate = annual_rate / 12 / 100\n    if monthly_rate == 0:\n        emi = principal / months\n    else:\n        emi = principal * monthly_rate * (1 + monthly_rate)**months / ((1 + monthly_rate)**months - 1)\n    return f\"Monthly EMI: ₹{emi:.2f}\"\n\ntools = [convert_usd_to_inr, calculate_emi]\n\n# Create the agent\nagent = create_react_agent(model=llm, tools=tools)\n\n# Run the agent\nresult = agent.invoke({\n    \"messages\": [(\"human\", \"Convert 250 USD to INR and calculate the EMI for a ₹500000 loan at 10% for 24 months.\")]\n})\n\nprint(\"=== Final Answer ===\")\nprint(result[\"messages\"][-1].content)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-13T07:34:56.396809Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-13T07:34:56.397169Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-13T07:34:56.767195Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-13T07:34:56.397123Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-13T07:34:56.766298Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.969989,"end_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:32.492858+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:31.522869+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[],"trusted":true},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"/tmp/ipykernel_55/2792736027.py:23: LangGraphDeprecatedSinceV10: create_react_agent has been moved to `langchain.agents`. Please update your import to `from langchain.agents import create_agent`. Deprecated in LangGraph V1.0 to be removed in V2.0.\n  agent = create_react_agent(model=llm, tools=tools)\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"=== Final Answer ===\nThe conversion of 250 USD to INR is approximately ₹20750.00. The monthly EMI for a ₹500000 loan at 10% for 24 months is ₹20855.04.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":36},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"7. Memory example","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.003368,"end_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:32.499523+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:32.496155+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"from langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate, MessagesPlaceholder\nfrom langchain_core.runnables.history import RunnableWithMessageHistory\nfrom langchain_community.chat_message_histories import ChatMessageHistory\n\nprompt_with_history = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\n    (\"system\", \"You are a helpful assistant.\"),\n    MessagesPlaceholder(variable_name=\"history\"),\n    (\"human\", \"{input}\"),\n])\n\nchain = prompt_with_history | llm | StrOutputParser()\nstore = {}\n\ndef get_session_history(session_id: str):\n    if session_id not in store:\n        store[session_id] = ChatMessageHistory()\n    return store[session_id]\n\nwith_message_history = RunnableWithMessageHistory(\n    chain,\n    get_session_history,\n    input_messages_key=\"input\",\n    history_messages_key=\"history\",\n)\n\nconfig = {\"configurable\": {\"session_id\": \"user_1\"}}\nresp1 = with_message_history.invoke({\"input\": \"Hi, my name is Shreyash Raut.\"}, config=config)\nprint(f\"Assistant: {resp1}\")\n\nresp2 = with_message_history.invoke({\"input\": \"What is my name?\"}, config=config)\nprint(f\"Assistant: {resp2}\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-13T07:34:56.76887Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-13T07:34:56.769375Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-13T07:34:56.935751Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-13T07:34:56.769346Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-13T07:34:56.934816Z"},"papermill":{"duration":1.407573,"end_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:33.910332+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:32.502759+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[],"trusted":true},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Assistant: Hello Shreyash Raut, it's nice to meet you. Is there something I can help you with or would you like to chat?\nAssistant: Your name is Shreyash Raut.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":37},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Vector Store Implementation (FAISS + HuggingFace)","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.004298,"end_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:33.923671+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:33.919373+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"from langchain_huggingface import HuggingFaceEmbeddings\nfrom langchain_community.vectorstores import FAISS\nfrom langchain_core.documents import Document\nfrom langchain_text_splitters import RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter\nfrom langchain_core.runnables import RunnablePassthrough\n\n# 1. Knowledge Base\ntech_docs = [\n    Document(page_content=\"The Model Context Protocol (MCP) allows AI agents to interact with local tools safely.\"),\n    Document(page_content=\"LangChain's LCEL allows for declarative composition of chains.\")\n]\n\n# 2. Split and Embed\nsplitter = RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(chunk_size=100, chunk_overlap=10)\nchunks = splitter.split_documents(tech_docs)\nembeddings = HuggingFaceEmbeddings(model_name=\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\")\nvector_db = FAISS.from_documents(chunks, embeddings)\n\n# 3. RAG Chain\nrag_template = \"\"\"Answer the question based only on the context:\n{context}\n\nQuestion: {question}\"\"\"\nrag_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_template(rag_template)\n\nrag_chain = (\n    {\"context\": vector_db.as_retriever(), \"question\": RunnablePassthrough()}\n    | rag_prompt\n    | llm\n    | StrOutputParser()\n)\n\nprint(\"--- RAG Result ---\")\nprint(rag_chain.invoke(\"How does MCP help AI agents?\"))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-13T07:34:56.937004Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-13T07:34:56.93749Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-13T07:34:58.501747Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-13T07:34:56.937417Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-13T07:34:58.500968Z"},"papermill":{"duration":18.042113,"end_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:51.96974+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-13T06:08:33.927627+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[],"trusted":true},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"Loading weights:   0%|          | 0/103